      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/ncv",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "NCV Level 4 — manufactured solution convergence order confirmed for all relevant PDE operators",
        "description": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) must confirm second-order spatial convergence for momentum, continuity, and scalar transport operators used in hemolysis model."
      },
      "rationale": "MMS convergence confirmed for momentum and continuity operators (second-order). However, the power-law hemolysis scalar transport operator achieves only 1.7-order convergence on the finest grid tested, falling short of the formal second-order criterion. This gap is explicitly flagged; the 0.3-order deficit is attributed to near-wall interpolation stencil truncation in high-shear regions. Sensitivity analysis shows the hemolysis index prediction is insensitive to this deficit at the spatial resolutions used in the COU (see hasSensitivityAnalysis). Offset rationale provided at DecisionRecord."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/disc-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/disc-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error Level 4 — GCI < 5% on all QOIs at operating envelope extremes",
        "description": "Grid Convergence Index must be below 5% for velocity magnitude, wall shear stress, and hemolysis index at all 5 operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "GCI for velocity magnitude and wall shear stress is below 5% at all operating points (range: 1.2%–4.8%). GCI for hemolysis index reaches 7.3% at the highest-speed operating point (6000 RPM, 5 L/min) due to thin boundary layer resolution constraints. This exceedance is explicitly documented with a 95% confidence interval on hemolysis index of ±9.2% at that point. The wide bound is honestly reported and propagated into the Monte Carlo UQ ensemble. Offset rationale provided at DecisionRecord."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/test-conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/test-conditions",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions Level 4 — in-vitro conditions match COU operating envelope within stated tolerances",
        "description": "Fluid viscosity, density, inlet flow waveform, and rotational speed in validation experiments must match COU conditions within ±5% for each parameter."
      },
      "rationale": "In-vitro validation experiments used bovine blood analog (glycerol-water, matched viscosity 3.5 cP ±0.1 cP), pump geometry identical to CFD geometry (CMM-verified), and flow rates within ±2% of target. All 5 operating points reproduced within stated tolerance. Achieved level 4 confirmed."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/output-comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/output-comparison",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison Level 4 — QOI predictions within experimental uncertainty at ≥4 of 5 operating points",
        "description": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index must fall within combined experimental and numerical uncertainty bounds at a minimum of 4 out of 5 operating points."
      },
      "rationale": "CFD predictions fall within combined uncertainty bounds at 3 of 5 operating points. At operating points 4 and 5 (highest flow rates), predicted hemolysis index exceeds the upper experimental uncertainty bound by 12% and 18% respectively. These discrepancies are honestly documented and attributed to turbulence model deficiency in the volute diffuser region. The model consistently over-predicts hemolysis (conservative direction for patient safety). Achieved level 3 reflects this shortfall; offset rationale at DecisionRecord addresses the conservative bias."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/qoi-relevance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/qoi-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QOI relevance Level 4 — hemolysis index directly maps to clinical endpoint",
        "description": "The QOI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be the same metric used in the clinical acceptance criterion and must be computed by an established power-law model traceable to published literature."
      },
      "rationale": "NIH computed using the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model, which is the same metric specified in FDA guidance for hemolysis evaluation. Direct mapping to clinical threshold confirmed. Achieved level 4."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/validation-relevance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/validation-relevance",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation relevance Level 5 — validation geometry, fluid, and operating conditions identical to COU",
        "description": "Validation must use the same pump geometry, blood analog properties, and operating envelope as the intended COU with no extrapolation beyond the validated domain."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation geometry is the FDA generic centrifugal pump, identical to COU geometry. Blood analog properties match within tolerance. However, validation experiments were conducted at sea-level atmospheric pressure whereas the COU specifies implanted device conditions (approximately 760 mmHg inlet pressure). The pressure difference introduces a minor dissolved-gas effect on blood analog viscosity not captured in validation. This gap reduces achieved level to 4 (one below required level 5). The effect is quantified via sensitivity analysis and shown to alter hemolysis index by less than 3%. Offset rationale at DecisionRecord."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/numerical-solver-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/numerical-solver-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error Level 4 — iterative convergence residuals below 1e-5 for all equations",
        "description": "All governing equation residuals must reach 1e-5 or below before solution is accepted; mass imbalance must be below 0.01% of inlet mass flow."
      },
      "rationale": "All simulations converged to residuals below 1e-6 (momentum, continuity, turbulence). Mass imbalance confirmed below 0.005% at all operating points. Achieved level 4 confirmed."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/use-error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/use-error",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Use error Level 4 — independent review of simulation setup and post-processing scripts",
        "description": "An independent reviewer (not the simulation analyst) must verify boundary condition setup, meshing parameters, and post-processing scripts against the simulation plan."
      },
      "rationale": "Independent review completed by a second FDA CDRH analyst. Boundary conditions, mesh parameters, and post-processing scripts verified against the pre-registered simulation plan. Two minor discrepancies identified and corrected before final results were accepted. Achieved level 4."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/model-form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/model-form",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form Level 5 — turbulence and hemolysis constitutive models validated against high-fidelity reference data specific to blood pump flows",
        "description": "The turbulence closure (SST k-omega) and hemolysis power-law model must each be validated against LES or DNS reference data for rotating blood pump geometries, demonstrating the model form is appropriate for the COU flow regime."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence closure is the best-available RANS model for rotating machinery and has been validated against PIV data for the FDA pump benchmark (good agreement in bulk flow). However, no LES or DNS reference exists for this specific geometry at MRL 5 conditions, and the hemolysis power-law model carries inherent epistemic uncertainty in the stress exponent (literature range: 1.9–2.4 for the Giersiepen-Wurzinger coefficients). Monte Carlo sampling over this coefficient range yields a 95% confidence interval on NIH of ±31%, which is wide and explicitly reported. Achieved level 3 reflects this fundamental model-form limitation. This is the primary driver of low overall confidence and is the central item in the offset rationale."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/model-inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/model-inputs",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs Level 4 — all material properties and boundary conditions characterized with uncertainty bounds from direct measurement",
        "description": "Blood analog viscosity, density, and inlet velocity profile must each be characterized from direct measurement with stated uncertainty; inlet turbulence intensity must be bounded by sensitivity analysis."
      },
      "rationale": "Viscosity and density measured directly (±2%). Inlet velocity profile measured by PIV (±5%). Inlet turbulence intensity is not directly measured; a literature range of 1%–8% is used and propagated via sensitivity analysis. The wide turbulence intensity range introduces a ±14% uncertainty contribution to hemolysis index predictions at high-shear operating points. This is honestly documented and included in the Monte Carlo ensemble. Achieved level 3 because one key input (turbulence intensity) is not directly measured."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/factor/cou2/test-samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
